4 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
5 Sec. 1. STATE TREASURER; MEDICAL DEBT RELIEF;
6 APPROPRIATION
7 (a) The sum of $1,000,000.00 is appropriated to the State Treasurer from
8 the General Fund in fiscal year 2026 for the purpose of contracting with a
9 nonprofit entity to acquire and repay certain medical debts incurred by
10 Vermont residents as set forth in this section.
11 (b) The State Treasurer shall ensure that the entity with which the Treasurer
12 contracts under this section will:
13 (1) purchase the medical debt of eligible debtors from health care
14 providers at fair market value;
15 (2) abolish the debt with no cost or tax consequences for the debtor; and
16 (3) coordinate with the health care provider or collections agency to
17 ensure that any adverse information resulting from the medical debt is removed
18 from the debtor’s consumer credit report following the contractor’s purchase
19 and abolition of the debt.
20 (c) In order to be eligible for repayment of medical debt under this section,
21 the following conditions must be met:
